{
  "texts": [
    "HPL: histomorphological Phenotype Learning through selfsupervised learning and community detection HPL discovers histomorphological phenotypes (HPs), i.e.",
    "distinct morphological tissue patterns, in large collections of whole-slide images (WSI) by employing an unbiased, self-supervised deep learning approach in which training does not require any label or annotations to be provided by expert pathologists.",
    "Once these distinct patterns are identified, any new WSI obtained from a patient sample can be characterized by the patterns it contains.",
    "This allows expert pathologists to assess quantitatively the composition of new samples in terms of histomorphological patterns.",
    "Figure 1 outlines the entire HPL methodology."
  ]
}